ge=EN>NOR Bard</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.dianarae.dreamhost.com/EQ/spin.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Wog</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>20</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>3/13/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>7:18:20 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.dianarae.dreamhost.com/EQ/bardpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">6-member rule question</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">While I see and agree with the reasoning behind the rule (however unfortunate it may be), I find myself agreeing to the allusion that Evilrulz made in the Guild Reps folder (ie: the number is too low considering the amount of planes-capable folks needed to even have posting rights).<br>
An alternative solution to this could be 6 members from posting entities, and perhaps 10 or so from a non-posting entity.  (Mileage may vary, price includes TT&amp;L, please consult your physician before raiding Planes)<br>
This in turn would help keep guilds in check as to trying to cheat the system while allowing more leeway fro guilds that may not have enough Planes-capable members to get posting status or be attractive enough for an alliance.<br>
<br>
Comments?  Thoughts?  Hopes?  Dreams?</font><P><img src="http://www.dianarae.dreamhost.com/EQ/gnolls.jpg"><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubiasschmias.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bias Schmias</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Glossolalia/CTA</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>218</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>3/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>12:16:57 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: 6-member rule question</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My opinion on the rules, whatever the form they take.<br>
<br>
Remember, I'm leaving the server, so my opinion is worth the paper you print it on.<br>
<br>
There have already been lovely little flamewars &amp; accusations and threats thrown around on all sides because the rules 'weren't clear', or because group A thought they meant 1 thing and group B thought they meant another.<br>
<br>
Keep It Simple.<br>
<br>
Make it a 6 person rule across the board, or remove it entirely.  Or make it a 10 person rule across the board.  doesn't matter to me.<br>
<br>
But don't make rules that start reading like nested loops.<br>
<br>
IF GUILD ismember PLANE_GUILD<br>
     {<br>
      MAX_INVITES = 6;<br>
     }<br>
ELSEIF GUILD !ismember PLANE_GUILD &amp;&amp; !ismember PLANE_ALLIANCE<br>
     {<br>
      MAX_INVITES = 6 - (sum ALLIANCE_INVITES)<br>
     }<br>
ELSE<br>
    MAX_INVITES = 10<br>
<br>
etc, etc.<br>
<br>
That's crazy talk.  Works great in the dev world, but won't work here.<br>
<br>
Here's a rule that's simple, not open for interpretation, and reduces friction between people since we can't all just agree to 'respect' raids for a variety of reasons (sample size, time constraints, etc)<br>
<br>
1 - A maximum of 6 people from any 1 guild or posting alliance may be invited on your raid.  People lacking guild tags are not subject to this restriction.<br>
<br>
Still pretty damn wordy, really.  <br>
<br>
Depending on how hot people felt about most of the multi-guild posting alliances, you could arguably strip the rule down to just<br>
<br>
1 - A maximum of 6 people from any 1 guild may be invited on your raid.  Nonguilded players are not subject to this rule.<br>
<br>
Anyway.  sleepy time now.<br>
<br>
Bias</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unyca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyca</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Spirit of Tunare</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>178</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>3/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>5:19:48 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.rockcitynews.com/art/artstill/valwarriorfem1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: 6-member rule question</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Edited out</font><P>Nycah Aries'Syrensong<BR>
